Format of Casio fx-7700GB CAS file.

CAS file consists of several sections, that always start with the ':' (0x3A)
and end with a checksum byte. 

The first section is always 40 bytes of header:
 0 - 0x3A ':'
 1 - 0x50 'P'
 2 - 0x31 '1' when containing a single program
     0x5A 'Z' when containing all programs

   5-byte Subheader:
 3 - 0x00 
 4 - MSB of the payload size
 5 - LSB of the payload size
 6 - MODE bits
    0 - Unknown
    1 - Statistics data
    2 - Matrix mode
    3 - Unknown
    4 - Standard deviation
    5 - Linear regression
    6 - Base-N
    7 - Draw Statistics Graph
 7 - 0x00

 8 .. 19 - 12 bytes, usually 0xFF (Might contain filename as a comment?)
20 .. 38 - 19 bytes, usually 0xFF, maybe unused?
39 - Sum( bytes 1 to 38 ) % 256 (Modulo 256).


File with all programs has the programs directory in the second section:
 0 - 0x3A ':'
 1 .. 190
   38 5-byte subheaders for every program
   0 - 0x00
   1 - MSB of the nth program size
   2 - LSB of the nth program size
   3 - Mode bits
   4 - 0x00
 191 - Sum( bytes 1 to 190 ) % 256 (Modulo 256).


File with all programs has the programs in the third section:
 0   - 0x3A ':'
 1  ... N bytes for all 38 programs, every program is terminated with 0xFF,
	  empty program is indicated with a single 0xFF.
 N+1 - Sum( bytes 1 to N ) % 256 (Modulo 256).


File with only one program has the program in the second section:
 0   - 0x3A ':'
 1  ... N program bytes
 N+1 - 0xFF
 N+2 - Sum( bytes 1 to N+1 ) % 256 (Modulo 256).

